<paragraph blockId="56.[1974,2559,2689,3107]" pageId="56" pageNumber="671">
Until 2005, the Upemba Lechwe was treated as a taxonomically indistinct subpopulation of 
<taxonomicName box="[2105,2205,2885,2910]" class="Mammalia" family="Bovidae" genus="Kobus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="56" pageNumber="671" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="leche">K. leche</taxonomicName>
, but it has recently been elevated to species status. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
